					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is an incomplete and damaged inscription. It seems to record an endowment of land after purchase, for burning a lamp and for offerings and worship to the goddess in the temple, by a resident of Tañjāvūr. Mention is made of a field called <hi rend="bold">Irumuḍi-Chōḷa-vayakkal.</hi> This is probably assignable to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rajēndra-Chōḷa I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
